ng zu nehmen, oder muss der Trennungsgrundsatz als eine zentrale ökonomische Funktion und Legitimation des Unternehmensverbunds erhalten bleiben? Diese und andere Fragen zu aktuellen Entwicklungen im Konzernrecht werden in diesem Band beantwortet.  aTo what extent are German parent companies responsible for their foreign subsidiaries? In cases of misconduct on the part of the subsidiary, must the entire corporate group take responsibility or does the principle of separation have validity as a central economic function and legitimation of the corporate group? This volume addresses these and further questions on current developments in group law.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aHolding companieszEuropean Union countries. 0aHolding companieszGermany. 0aSubsidiary corporationszEuropean Union countries. 0aSubsidiary corporationszGermany. 4aKonzernmutter. 4aKonzernrecht. 4aTochtergesellschaft.  aGroup law.  aparent company.  asubsidiary.1 aBahlinger, Simon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBenz, Nina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBergmann, Alfred, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDrescher, Ingo, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aEngert, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFleischer, Holger, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFülbier, Rolf Uwe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGassen, Joachim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoette, Wulf, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHarbarth, Stephan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHommelhoff, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/